---

<section id="why" class="py-24 bg-gray-900/50">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <h2 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl font-bold text-center text-white mb-12">Why We Built STOA</h2>

    <div class="space-y-8 text-lg text-gray-300">
      <!-- Problem 1 -->
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="text-red-400 text-2xl shrink-0">X</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">API Gateways weren't built for AI</h3>
          <p>Traditional gateways don't understand MCP, can't meter AI tokens, and treat agent traffic like any other HTTP call.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 2 -->
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="text-red-400 text-2xl shrink-0">X</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">MCP is powerful but ungoverned</h3>
          <p>The Model Context Protocol lets AI agents call tools — but who controls access? How do you audit AI actions?</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem 3 -->
      <div class="flex gap-4">
        <span class="text-red-400 text-2xl shrink-0">X</span>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">Vendor lock-in is getting worse</h3>
          <p>Most API platforms lock you in. Open source shouldn't mean "open until you need enterprise features."</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Solution -->
      <div class="mt-12 p-6 bg-gray-800 rounded-xl border border-green-800/50">
        <div class="flex gap-4">
          <span class="text-green-400 text-2xl shrink-0">
            <svg class="w-7 h-7" fill="none" viewBox="0 0 24 24" stroke="currentColor">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M5 13l4 4L19 7" />
            </svg>
          </span>
          <div>
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-white mb-2">STOA: The missing governance layer</h3>
            <p>One platform for traditional APIs and AI agents. Same policies, same audit trail. Open source core, no bait-and-switch.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
